f=Brand Studio/atlas/marketplace/layout-composition/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "layout-composition", selected fulfill catalog's "canvas-design" slot composition layout craft. Matches catalog protocol nearly verbatim ("Grid hierarchy first Contrast focal point Whitespace element" skill's grid systems, visual-hierarchy priority ordering, active-whitespace sections). Chosen over ArnavPuri/designskills (web-implementation-leaning) atelier-layout (CSS-implementation-heavy) because one framed making layout DECISIONS, which atlas's altitude CSS snippets carries illustrations, usable deliverable web, ignorable it's social graphic deck. --> · h2:When to Activate=Making layout decisions new screen component, Diagnosing layout feels crowded, inconsistent, confusing, Choosing grid system design system, Evaluating visual hierarchy design review, Deciding place primary CTA · h2:Gestalt Principles=principles describe humans automatically group visual elements. Use them deliberately. · h3:1. Proximity=`APPLY: Group related form fields together, separate from unrelated sections. \· Keep labels within 8px of their inputs; put 32px between field groups. \·  \· COMMON MISTAKE: Equal spacing between everything — no visual grouping.` · h3:1. Proximity=Elements close together perceived group. Distance creates separation. · h3:2. Alignment=`APPLY: Align all body text to the same left edge. Align card content to a grid. \· Mixing left-aligned and center-aligned text in one section creates visual noise. \·  \· COMMON MISTAKE: Centering headings while left-aligning body — breaks axis consistency.` · h3:2. Alignment=Elements aligned shared invisible axis appear ordered related. · h3:3. Contrast=`APPLY: Primary button: filled, bold color. Secondary: outlined, muted. \· H1: 3× larger than body. Key metric: 4× larger than label. \·  \· COMMON MISTAKE: All buttons the same size and color — no hierarchy. \· "Everything is bold" — when everything is emphasized, nothing is.` · h3:3. Contrast=Differences size, color, weight create emphasis hierarchy. · h3:4. Repetition (Consistency)=`APPLY: All cards have the same padding, border radius, shadow. \· All section headers use the same H2 style. \· All CTAs are the same button component. \·  \· COMMON MISTAKE: Slightly different card styles across pages — feels inconsistent,` · h3:4. Repetition (Consistency)=Repeating visual elements across composition creates unity reduces cognitive load. · h3:5. Enclosure=`APPLY: Cards use a container with border/shadow to define a unit of content. \· Modal dialogs use a contrasting background to separate from page. \· Sidebar uses a different background to separate from main content. \·  \· COMMON MISTAKE: Using both a border AND a shadow — double enclosure is redundant.` · h3:5. Enclosure=boundary (card, background, border, shadow) groups elements separates them surroundings. · h3:Priority ordering=`1. SIZE         — largest elements are read first; 3× size = highest priority \· 2. WEIGHT       — bold vs. regular; use weight to indicate importance within same size \· 3. COLOR        — primary color = primary action; muted = secondary \· 4. POSITION     — top-left is read first (F-pattern); center commands attention \· 5. CONTRAST     — high contrast = foreground; low contrast = recedes` · h3:Priority ordering=Build hierarchy tools, descending effectiveness: · h3:Maximum hierarchy levels=`Level 1: Primary heading / Key metric — most prominent \· Level 2: Body text / Secondary labels — readable, not competing \· Level 3: Caption / Helper text — clearly subordinate \·  \· WRONG: 5 different font sizes, 3 different colors, 4 different weights in one card` · h3:Maximum hierarchy levels=Use maximum distinct visual levels screen: · h3:Hierarchy failure modes=\| Symptom \| Cause \| Fix \| · h3:Hierarchy failure modes=\|---------\|-------\|-----\| · h3:Hierarchy failure modes=\| "I don't know where to look" \| No single primary element \| Increase size/contrast of one element 2-3× \| · h3:Hierarchy failure modes=\| "It all looks the same" \| Insufficient contrast between levels \| Widen the size or weight gap \| · h3:Hierarchy failure modes=\| "It feels cluttered" \| Too many level-1 elements \| Demote secondary items to level 2 \| · ch:list=Grid system chosen content type (column baseline modular), Spacing values 8px multiples, Proximity: related elements ≤8px apart; section gaps ≥32px, elements align shared column edge (no floating elements), Contrast: primary button visually dominates secondary, Repetition: card components, buttons, headings visually consistent, Enclosure: card uses border shadow,, Section gaps macro (80-120px), micro, Exactly one primary CTA screen, Maximum hierarchy levels screen, Active whitespace used isolate primary focal element